This entire directory is called the VitaOS-Libre project. However, each
directory in the Sources directory is a subproject of the VitaOS-Libre
project.

There exist the BitBitJump-64Bit, HaltingProblemSolutionIdea,
QuantumTunnelingTransistorRNGIdea, VitaFPGAArch,
VitaFPGAArchSynthesizer, VitaFPGAEmulator and VitaKernel subprojects.

The Builds directory contains the binaries made from the source code in
the VitaOS-Libre project.

The VitaOS-Libre project is licensed under The VitaSet License.

It would be appreciated if you could donate or invest in VitaSet LLC,
so that it would be possible to create computer chips with the Vita
FPGA Architecture and a CPU that does cryptographic signature checking
of a boot bitstream before loading it fully into the Vita FPGA
Architecture. The CPU can also have battery-backed Sram bits to hold
a Public and a Private Asymmetric Cryptographic Key, powered by one or
two coin-cell batteries. The keys can be wiped by taking out both of
the coin-cell batteries, or they can be kept and have the coin-cell
batteries replaced by replacing one coin-cell battery and then the
other coin-cell battery.
